{
  "stem": "21482.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we would be downstairs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The children would be downstairs watching, making sure that the Germans were not coming.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was like two kids were out on a street, and two kids would be like on a second floor so that if we saw the Germans coming, we could call up and the other kids would run into the apartment and tell the people.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we were lucky, and they didn't come.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They never came?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They never came while we prayed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When they came, they were-- when they came they were looking to take gold and silver and brass and furs.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had a little dog, and we were not allowed to have dogs.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One night-- this was even before we had to wear the armbands.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was outside one evening with the little dog.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the German patrol came by and said, what are you doing out on a street?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They didn't know at the time I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I didn't have to wear a star.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I told them I had to take the dog out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they didn't, you know, do anything to me, but it scared my parents enough to give the dog away to the Polish woman that used to bring milk to the house in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "After a few months, the Polish people were not allowed to do any business with the Jews, and they couldn't bring any milk.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I think the only milk you could buy was from the peasants who used to come and sell to the houses.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So we had a woman that used to come and bring milk every day.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we had no refrigerators, no iceboxes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We started to wear the armband probably at the end of 1939.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
